'''按服務收費'''（{{lang-en|Fee-for-service}}，FFS）是一種收費模式，把提供的服務解開，針對其中的每一項服務，單獨計算收費。

在[[醫療衛生|醫療衛生]]領域，這種模式會激勵醫生提供更多的服務，因為收費是根據醫療的次數，而不是根據醫療最終的品質來做決定。然而，{{link-en|按績效計算報酬|Pay for performance (healthcare)}}是否能有效改善醫療的品質，則也還沒確切的證據來表明它是成功，或是失敗的。<ref name="Doubts about Pay for Performance in Health Care">{{Cite web|url=https://hbr.org/2013/10/doubts-about-pay-for-performance-in-health-care|title=Doubts About Pay-for-Performance in Health Care|first1=Andrew M.|last1=Ryan|first2=Rachel M.|last2=Werner|date=2013-10-09|via=hbr.org|accessdate=2020-09-06|archive-date=2019-03-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190328172131/https://hbr.org/2013/10/doubts-about-pay-for-performance-in-health-care|dead-url=no}}</ref>同樣的，當患者的費用是經由醫療保險覆蓋（{{le|費用分攤|cost sharing}}）的時候，就會激勵他們採用任何可能有益的醫療服務，按服務收費的成本因此會增加，把綜合式護理的功效削弱。各界已經嘗試過、建議過、或發動過各種改革措施，企圖把這種支付方式的影響降低（例如轉向[[捆綁式付款|捆綁式付款]]和[[論人計酬支付|論人計酬支付]]等方式）。在論人計酬付費的情況下，醫師沒執行療程（包括必要的程序）的動機，因為他們不會因做這些事而得到額外的報酬。

FFS是美國主要的醫師收費方式。<ref name="USapproaches"/>在{{link-en|日本醫療衛生系統|health care system in Japan}}中，FFS與全國性的定價機制（{{link-en|全數支付者統一定價|all-payer rate setting}}）混合使用，以便達到控制成本的目的。<ref name="Sick">{{cite episode |title=Sick around the world |series={{tsl|en|Frontline (U.S. TV series)||Frontline}} |network=[[公共广播电视公司|公共广播电视公司]] |airdate=April 15, 2008 |minutes=17 |url=https://www.pbs.org/wgbh/pages/frontline/sickaroundtheworld/ |access-date=2020-09-06 |archive-date=2019-09-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190910044846/https://www.pbs.org/wgbh/pages/frontline/sickaroundtheworld/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>
 
==醫療衛生==
在[[醫療保險|醫療保險]]和醫療衛生的行業中，如果醫生和其他[[醫事人員|醫事人員]]根據每一項服務（例如門診服務、測試、療程、或其他服務）分開收取費用，就是FFS的觀念。<ref name="FEHB">[http://www.opm.gov/insure/glossary/index.asp FEHB Glossary.] {{Wayback|url=http://www.opm.gov/insure/glossary/index.asp |date=20121101160814 }} Retrieved May 31, 2006.</ref>服務發生之後才會收款。FFS有導致醫療衛生成本被提高的作用。<ref name="Realignment">{{Cite journal | author=[[Winnie_Chi-Man_Yip|Winnie Chi-Man Yip]], {{tsl|en|William Hsiao||William Hsiao}}, [[Qingyue_Meng|Qingyue Meng]], [[Wen_Chen|Wen Chen]] & [[Xiaoming_Sun|Xiaoming Sun]] | title = Realignment of incentives for health-care providers in China | journal=[[柳葉刀_(雜誌)|柳葉刀 (雜誌)]] | volume = 375 | issue = 9720 | pages = 1120–1130 |date=March 2010 | doi = 10.1016/S0140-6736(10)60063-3 | pmid = 20346818}}</ref>
 
FFS有刺激患者過度使用[[不必要的醫療照顧|不必要的醫療照顧]]的可能<ref name="Perfect Storm">{{Cite journal | author = {{tsl|en|Ezekiel J. Emanuel||Ezekiel J. Emanuel}} & {{tsl|en|Victor R. Fuchs||Victor R. Fuchs}} | title = The perfect storm of overutilization | journal = [[美国医学会杂志|美国医学会杂志]] | volume = 299 | issue = 23 | pages = 2789–2791 | date = June 2008 | doi = 10.1001/jama.299.23.2789 | pmid = 18560006 | url = http://www.ipalc.org/Healthcare_Policy/The%20Perfect%20Storm%20of%20Overutilization%20%28JAMA%202008%29.pdf | dead-url = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20090902053119/http://www.ipalc.org/Healthcare_Policy/The%20Perfect%20Storm%20of%20Overutilization%20%28JAMA%202008%29.pdf | archivedate = 2009-09-02 }}</ref>，高額費用因而產生，對於患者可能有財務上的[[利益衝突|利益衝突]]<ref>{{cite journal |author=[[Ronald_M._Green|Ronald M. Green]] |date=July–August 1990 |title=Medical joint-venturing: An ethical perspective |journal={{tsl|en|Hastings Center Report||Hastings Center Report}} |volume=20 |issue=4 |pages=22–6 |pmid=2211082}}</ref>。
 
FFS會激勵醫生增加提供服務。<ref name="CommentOn"/>如果費用由第三方買單，則患者（以及醫生）不會有費用方面的顧慮。<ref>{{Cite journal | author={{tsl|en|Victor R. Fuchs||Victor R. Fuchs}} | title = Eliminating 'waste' in health care | journal=[[美国医学会杂志|美国医学会杂志]] | volume = 302 | issue = 22 | pages = 2481–2482 |date=December 2009 | doi = 10.1001/jama.2009.1821 | pmid = 19996406}}</ref>患者在由第三方付款時，當然歡迎接受服務，因為"當人們想要得到心中所想的產品或服務，又無需顧慮成本時，他們更會多加利用。 "<ref>{{cite news |title=Why Medicare Patients See the Doctor Too Much |author1=Merrill Matthews |author2=Mark Litow |newspaper=[[华尔街日报|华尔街日报]] |date=2011-07-11 |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424052702304760604576428300875828790 |accessdate=2011-07-22 |archive-date=2015-09-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150916103435/http://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424052702304760604576428300875828790 |dead-url=no }}</ref>
 
有證據顯示，接受FFS模式付費的{{le|初級照護醫師|Primary care physician}}，會比按論人計酬支付或僅為受薪的醫生，為患者提供更多的療程。<ref>{{cite journal  |vauthors=Gosden T, Forland F, Kristiansen IS, etal |title=Capitation, salary, fee-for-service and mixed systems of payment: effects on the behaviour of primary care physicians |journal=Cochrane Database Syst Rev |issue=3 |pages=CD002215 |year=2000 |pmid=10908531 |doi=10.1002/14651858.CD002215 |url=}}</ref>FFS模式會激勵初級照護醫師投資在[[影像診斷學|影像診斷]]診所，並做[[醫師自我推薦|醫師自我推薦]]來創造額外收入。<ref name="Healthier"/>
 
私人執業醫師和小型診所最容易受到政府和第三方付款人降低服務費用報銷的影響。不斷上升的監管要求，例如購買和安裝昂貴的[[電子健康記錄|電子健康記錄]]設備，以及政府為糾正Medicare欺詐和濫用行為所做的各種管制措施，導致這些人或機構的行政管理費用膨脹，收入受到侵蝕。<ref>{{cite web
 | url = https://www.researchgate.net/publication/23273405_Despite_regulatory_changes_hospitals_cautious_in_helping_physicians_purchase_electronic_medical_records
 | title = Despite regulatory changes, hospitals cautious in helping physicians purchase electronic medical records
 | publisher = ResearchGate
 | date = October 2008
 | accessdate = 7 March 2021
 }}</ref>
 
雖然大多數業者的做法是屈從於需要看更多的病人，並增加服務的次數來維持收入，但也有許多醫生在尋求替代模型作為解決方案。除了基於價值的報銷模型（例如按績效計算報酬和{{link-en|盡責護理組織|accountable care organizations}}）（ACO）之外，對於舊有的禮賓服務和直接付款模式的興趣也再度興起。<ref>[http://www.physicianspractice.com/great-american-physician-survey/content/article/1462168/2100106 "Healthcare Reform Influencing Physicians' Career Choices"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.physicianspractice.com/great-american-physician-survey/content/article/1462168/2100106 |date=20120921034720 }} Aubrey Westgate, Physicians Practice, September 2012.</ref>當患者有更多的機會與醫生聯繫，並且醫生有更多的時間與患者共處時，像影像診斷和測試等的利用率就會下降。
 
FFS系統相對於協調式護理（或稱{{le|綜合式護理|Integrated care}}，如同[[梅奧醫院|梅奧醫院]]等機構所實施）的執行是一種障礙，因為它獎勵個別臨床醫生做單獨的治療。<ref>{{cite book |title=Building a Better Delivery System: A New Engineering/Health Care Partnership – Bridging the Quality Chasm |last=Lawrence |first=David |year=2005 |publisher=[[美国国家科学院|美国国家科学院]] |location=Washington, DC |isbn=978-0-309-65406-7 |page=99 |url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK22832/pdf/TOC.pdf#page=114 |access-date=2020-09-06 |archive-date=2020-09-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200906051449/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK22832/pdf/Bookshelf_NBK22832.pdf#page=114 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Episodes"/>在FFS系統之下，醫療機構不會給予需要高昂費用患者特別的注意。<ref name="Mass"/>往往給予特別注意的醫療機構僅利用電話診斷，不需住院，也不要透過911的緊急救護，即可解決患者的問題。<ref name="Mass"/><ref>{{cite news |title=The Hot Spotters: Can we lower medical costs by giving the neediest patients better care? |author=[[阿图·葛文德|阿图·葛文德]] |newspaper=[[紐約客|紐約客]] |date=2011-01-24 |url=http://www.newyorker.com/reporting/2011/01/24/110124fa_fact_gawande?currentPage=all |accessdate=2011-06-26 |archive-date=2011-07-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110714014955/http://www.newyorker.com/reporting/2011/01/24/110124fa_fact_gawande?currentPage=all |dead-url=no }}</ref>目前FFS仍是美國主要的醫療費用付款方式。<ref name="USapproaches"/>醫療機構的高級主管們對於由 FFS轉入[[管理式醫療護理|管理式醫療護理]]感到遺憾，認為轉變會把"以生產效率為導向的醫生，轉變為自我滿足，只拿薪水的打工族。" <ref name="USapproaches">{{Cite journal | author=[[Robert_A._Berenson|Robert A. Berenson]] & [[Eugene_C._Rich|Eugene C. Rich]] | title = US approaches to physician payment: the deconstruction of primary care | journal={{tsl|en|Journal of General Internal Medicine||Journal of General Internal Medicine}} | volume = 25 | issue = 6 | pages = 613–618 |date=June 2010 | doi = 10.1007/s11606-010-1295-z | pmid = 20467910 | pmc = 2869428}}</ref><ref name="CommentOn">{{cite journal| author=Chernew ME| title=Reforming payment for health care services: comment on "physicians' opinions about reforming reimbursement" | journal={{tsl|en|Arch Intern Med||Arch Intern Med}} | year= 2010 | volume= 170 | issue= 19 | pages= 1742–4 | pmid=20975021 | doi=10.1001/archinternmed.2010.377 | pmc= }}</ref>從FFS模式轉向綜合式護理之後，[[普通科醫生|普通科醫生]]的自主權降低。<ref name="Swiss">{{Cite journal | author=[[Peter_Zweifel|Peter Zweifel]] | title = Swiss experiment shows physicians, consumers want significant compensation to embrace coordinated care | journal={{tsl|en|Health Affairs (Project Hope)||Health Affairs (Project Hope)}} | volume = 30 | issue = 3 | pages = 510–518 |date=March 2011 | doi = 10.1377/hlthaff.2010.0954 | pmid = 21383370}}</ref>從FFS模式轉出後，患者對醫生的選擇受到限制，就像[[荷蘭|荷蘭]]嘗試轉移到協調式護理的結果一樣。<ref> Peter Zweifel (March 2011). "Swiss experiment shows physicians, consumers want significant compensation to embrace coordinated care". Health Affairs (Project Hope). 30 (3): 510–518. doi:10.1377/hlthaff.2010.0954. PMID 21383370.</ref>
 
當醫生無法為單項服務收費時，他就沒有提供服務的動機，尤其是如果當時有別的收費的機會。當專家對資料做評估（例如檢驗資料或者成像照片，稱為電子診斷（ e-referral））而不是親自見到患者，這種做法通常可提高醫療品質並同時降低成本。但是，"在私人FFS收費的背景下，專家對於收入損失的擔憂，變成是移往電子診斷的強大障礙，如果醫療計劃能夠補償專家處理電子診斷所花費的時間，這種障礙說不定可被克服。" <ref>{{Cite journal | author=[[Thomas_Bodenheimer|Thomas Bodenheimer]] | title = Coordinating care – a perilous journey through the health care system | journal=[[新英格兰医学杂志|新英格兰医学杂志]] | volume = 358 | issue = 10 | pages = 1064–1071 |date=March 2008 | doi = 10.1056/NEJMhpr0706165 | pmid = 18322289 | citeseerx = 10.1.1.527.4412 }}</ref>
 
在[[加拿大|加拿大]]，從1990年到2010年，按FFS收費的服務比例有大幅度轉變。<ref name="WorstRun"/>對55歲以下患者發生的護理費用減少，而對65歲以上患者的診斷服務費用則大幅增加。<ref name="WorstRun">{{cite journal |author=Rachel Mendleson |date=2010-10-25 |title=The Worst-Run Industry in Canada: Health Care |journal={{tsl|en|Canadian Business||Canadian Business}} |volume=83 |issue=17 |url=http://www.canadianbusiness.com/article/11248--the-worst-run-industry-in-canada-health-care |access-date=2020-09-06 |archive-date=2012-11-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121108110547/http://www.canadianbusiness.com/article/11248--the-worst-run-industry-in-canada-health-care |dead-url=yes }}</ref>

==改革==
從FFS轉向按績效計算報酬，有刺激在品質和效率改進的作用，以取代僅就數量做考慮的缺失。<ref name="Episodes">{{Cite journal | author={{tsl|en|Karen Davis (economist)||Karen Davis}} | title = Paying for care episodes and care coordination | journal=[[新英格兰医学杂志|新英格兰医学杂志]] | volume = 356 | issue = 11 | pages = 1166–1168 |date=March 2007 | doi = 10.1056/NEJMe078007 | pmid = 17360996 }}</ref> 除了[[梅奧醫院|梅奧醫院]]之外，其他醫療衛生系統，如[[賓西法尼亞州|賓西法尼亞州]]的{{link-en|Geisinger醫療系統|Geisinger Health System}}、[[猶他州|猶他州]]的{{link-en|Intermountain醫療機構|Intermountain Healthcare}}、[[俄亥俄州|俄亥俄州]]的{{link-en|克里夫蘭醫院|Cleveland Clinic}}、和{{link-en|凱撒醫療系統|Kaiser Permanente}}，它們運用協調式/綜合式護理式的系統來取代FFS系統，這種新的模式是根據治療患者的結果，在提供醫師們薪水之外，還有領取額外獎金的機會，。<ref name="Healthier">{{cite journal |author=Jeffery Kluger |date=2009-10-26 |title=A Healthier Way to Pay Doctors |journal=TIME |volume=174 |issue=16 |url=http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,1930501,00.html |pmid=19873802 |pages=36–40 |access-date=2020-09-06 |archive-date=2013-08-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130826135809/http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,1930501,00.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>協調式醫療與FFS相比，可以節省約50％的成本，但為付款人提供的長期節省可能不會超過40％。<ref name="Swiss"/>
 
盡責護理組織（ACO）是因《 PPACA》而設立的組織，目標是從FFS的付費模式轉向綜合式護理。<ref>{{cite news |title='Accountable care' expected to save millions for Medicare |author1=Phil Galewitz |author2=Jordan Rau |author3=Bara Vaida |newspaper={{tsl|en|Kaiser Health News||Kaiser Health News}} |publisher=McClatchy |date=2011-03-31 |url=http://www.mcclatchydc.com/2011/03/31/111354/accountable-care-expected-to-save.html |accessdate=2011-06-26 |archive-date=2011-05-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110505034522/http://www.mcclatchydc.com/2011/03/31/111354/accountable-care-expected-to-save.html |dead-url=yes }}</ref>但是ACO大致上是適合FFS的框架，並且不會完全放棄FFS的方式。<ref name="Some">{{Cite journal | author={{tsl|en|John K. Iglehart||John K. Iglehart}} | title = The ACO regulations – some answers, more questions | journal=[[新英格兰医学杂志|新英格兰医学杂志]] | volume = 364 | issue = 17 | pages = e35 |date=April 2011 | doi = 10.1056/NEJMp1103603 | pmid = 21488758 | url = }}</ref>這種做法顯示的是決策者試圖避免激起公眾的強烈抗議，就像在1990年代的管理式醫療護理組織所產生的，由於這項法案讓醫療機構有減少提供服務的動機。<ref name="Some"/>PPACA的目標是首先將FFS支付方式從Medicare移出，然後再由其他支付者移出。<ref>{{Cite journal | author={{tsl|en|Kenneth E. Thorpe||Kenneth E. Thorpe}} & [[Lydia_L._Ogden|Lydia L. Ogden]] | title = Analysis & commentary. The foundation that health reform lays for improved payment, care coordination, and prevention | journal={{tsl|en|Health Affairs (Project Hope)||Health Affairs (Project Hope)}} | volume = 29 | issue = 6 | pages = 1183–1187 |date=June 2010 | doi = 10.1377/hlthaff.2010.0415 | pmid = 20530352}}</ref>一項在[[瑞士|瑞士]]做的研究顯示，醫生希望在從FFS轉向綜合式護理模式之前，能大幅提高薪水，而患者的希望則是在選擇保險之前先降低保險費，研究結論暗示PPACA想達成目標的困難度<ref name="Swiss"/>
 
在中國大陸，由於FFS系統讓醫療服務成本高昂、效率低下、質量低劣，導致[[醫學倫理學|醫學倫理]]的沉淪，因此有改革方案被提出，用來調整醫療衛生機構的激勵機制。<ref name="Realignment"/>新的付款模式正在試驗中，包括加強醫學倫理，修改醫療機構的利潤動機，以及如果醫院保留住獲利的動機，則把對醫生的激勵措施從醫院的獲利目標分開處理。<ref name="Realignment"/>
 
在美國，1990年代從FFS轉向純粹論人計酬支付系統，引起患者和醫療衛生機構的強烈反彈。<ref name="Episodes"/>不論是什麼疾病，純論人計酬支付方式僅需按照患者人數支付固定費用，讓醫生會設法避開花費最高的患者（也是要花費醫生最多功夫的患者）。<ref name="BetterWays">{{Cite journal | author = [[Harold_D._Miller|Harold D. Miller]] | title = From volume to value: better ways to pay for health care | journal = {{tsl|en|Health Affairs (Project Hope)||Health Affairs (Project Hope)}} | volume = 28 | issue = 5 | pages = 1418–1428 |date=September–October 2009 | doi = 10.1377/hlthaff.28.5.1418 | pmid = 19738259}}</ref>為了避免陷入FFS和純粹論人計酬支付之間的陷阱，捆綁式付款和綜合式護理付款的模型被提出，用來取代。<ref name="BetterWays"/>2009年，[[麻薩諸塞州|麻薩諸塞州]]的醫療保健費用，因為在全美排名最前，在立法授權之下，找來十名醫療衛生專家組成工作小組（麻薩諸塞州支付改革委員會 (the Massachusetts Payment Reform Commission)），負責找出解決的方法；他們一致的結論是必須放棄FFS模型。<ref name="Mass"/>他們建議的計劃中包括一種類似捆綁式付款的付費方式。<ref name="Mass"/>美國沒有任何一州嘗試完全把FFS放棄。<ref name="Mass">{{cite news |title=To Lower Costs, Mass. May Restructure Doctor Pay |author=Richard Knox |newspaper={{tsl|en|Morning Edition||Morning Edition}} |publisher=[[全国公共广播电台|全国公共广播电台]] |date=2009-08-05 |url=https://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=111492444 |accessdate=2011-06-26 |archive-date=2011-10-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111026225824/http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=111492444 |dead-url=no }}</ref> No US state had attempted to do away with FFS.<ref name="Mass"/>
 
美國的[[聯邦醫療保險|聯邦醫療保險]]（Medicare）採用的是FFS的報銷方式 <ref>{{Cite journal | author=[[Peter_B._Bach|Peter B. Bach]] | title = Costs of cancer care: a view from the centers for Medicare and Medicaid services | journal={{tsl|en|Journal of Clinical Oncology||Journal of Clinical Oncology}} | volume = 25 | issue = 2 | pages = 187–190 |date=January 2007 | doi = 10.1200/JCO.2006.08.6116 | pmid = 17210938}}</ref> {{link-en|Medicare付款諮詢委員會|Medicare Payment Advisory Commission}}（MedPAC）在2011年中期向國會提交的報告中呼籲建立一種機制，用來抑制Medicare受益人不必要的醫療護理，從而減少FFS產生的高額支出。<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.courant.com/sdut-medicare-options-in-biden-budget-talks-get-boost-2011jun15-story.html |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2020-09-06 |archive-date=2020-09-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200906051355/https://www.courant.com/sdut-medicare-options-in-biden-budget-talks-get-boost-2011jun15-story.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>
 
==專利==
[[美國專利及商標局|美國專利及商標局]]的收費方式，使用的是FFS模式。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://thomas.loc.gov/cgi-bin/cpquery/T?&report=sr397&dbname=110& |title=Report on Departments of Commerce and Justice, Science, and Related Agencies Appropriations Bill, 2009 |publisher={{tsl|en|United States Senate Committee on Appropriations||United States Senate Committee on Appropriations}} |date=2008-06-23 |accessdate=2011-07-04 |quote=As a fee for service agency the USPTO operates in a business like model. |archive-date=2009-05-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090507155859/http://thomas.loc.gov/cgi-bin/cpquery/T?&report=sr397&dbname=110& |dead-url=no }}</ref>
 
==房地產==
在房地產的交易，也有用FFS收費來取代支付成交佣金的方式。用FFS的模式，經紀人可根據帶客戶參觀物件的次數，或是其他服務方面來收取費用。<ref>ABout.com Real Estate Business definitions http://realestate.about.com/od/df/g/deffeeforsvc.htm {{Wayback|url=http://realestate.about.com/od/df/g/deffeeforsvc.htm |date=20160420211435 }}</ref>
 
